sights.name: The Ukrainian State Museum of the Great Patriotic War
sights.orig_name: The Ukrainian State Museum of the Great Patriotic War
sights.quote: Vast war memorial sculpted by Vuchetych & a museum displaying exhibits about WWII in the Ukraine.

sights.name: Kiev Pechersk Lavra
sights.quote: Ornate religious buildings line this iconic monastic complex, known for its network of catacombs.

sights.name: Park Landscape Alley
sights.quote: Charming public park showcasing offbeat local artwork, including abstract sculptures & mosaics.

sights.name: The Motherland Monument
sights.quote: Huge statue atop of the National Museum of the History of the Great Patriotic War of 1941-1945.

sights.name: Golden Gate
sights.quote: 1980s replica of 11th-century Golden Gate, the main fortified entrance to the medieval city.

sights.name: St. Sophia's Cathedral
sights.quote: Orthodox cathedral, founded in 1037, with monastic buildings, a gilt cupola, necropolis and museum.

sights.name: Taras shevchenko park
sights.quote: Popular city park with a paved walking track, a playground, cafes & a restaurant.

sights.name: St. Volodymyr's Cathedral
sights.quote: Neo-Byzantine cathedral with bright yellow facade, opening to a gold-accented fresco-lined interior.

sights.name: Gorodetsky House
sights.quote: Landmark Art Nouveau building & Presidential residence with a gallery and animal sculptures.

sights.name: St. Andrew's Church
sights.quote: Lavish 18th-century baroque church sitting on a hill overlooking one of Kiev's oldest neighborhoods.

sights.name: Feofaniya park
sights.quote: Landscaped area with 5 lakes, woodland & paths, designated a state park for its biodiversity.

sights.name: St. Michael's Golden-Domed Monastery
sights.quote: Site comprising of a cathedral, bell tower, refectory & gates, all built in Ukrainian Baroque style.

sights.name: Oleg Antonov State Aviation Museum
sights.quote: Aviation museum with around 70 airplanes & helicopters plus air weapons, drones & aircraft engines.

sights.name: M. M. Hryshko National Botanical Garden
sights.orig_name: M. M. Hryshko National Botanical Garden
sights.quote: Extensive botanical gardens with a remarkable variety of flora, plus exotic plants in glasshouses.

sights.name: Mykhailo Bulgakov Museum-Memorial
sights.quote: Exhibition of items relating to the eponymous writer, in grand mansion where he lived for 13 years.

sights.name: Great Lavra Bell Tower
sights.quote: Iconic, 18th-century octagonal belfry of an ancient cave monastery, with city views from 96m up.

sights.name: St. Nicholas Roman Catholic Cathedral
sights.quote: Early 20th-century cathedral originally constructed to serve the city's growing Polish community.

sights.name: Mariyinsky Palace
sights.quote: Reconstructed Baroque palace & official residence of Ukraine's president, first completed in 1752.

sights.name: Pedestrian bridge over the Dnipro river
sights.orig_name: Pedestrian bridge over the Dnipro river
sights.quote: Illuminated at night, this footbridge has a bike lane & a bungee jump, plus sweeping city views.

sights.name: St. Cyril's Church
sights.quote: Cream-colored 12th-century place of Orthodox worship with an on-site museum of religious artworks.

sights.name: Insomnia Rooms of Fear Kiev - The haunted house Kyiv
sights.orig_name: Insomnia Комнаты Страха Киев - The haunted house Kyiv

sights.name: Mystetskyi Arsenal National Art and Culture Museum Complex
sights.orig_name: Mystetskyi Arsenal National Art and Culture Museum Complex

sights.name: Ukrainian National Chornobyl Museum
sights.quote: Museum detailing the Chernobyl nuclear disaster, with audio-visual exhibits, photos & documents.

sights.name: Mykola Siadrystyi Micro Miniatures Museum
sights.quote: Room with a collection of tiny artworks by miniaturist Mykola Syadristy, viewed through microscopes.

sights.name: Volodymyrska Hill
sights.quote: Sweeping views are the main draw at this hilltop park with a funicular & monument to St. Volodymyr.

sights.name: Bessarabsky Market
sights.quote: Food market in a historic building open round-the-clock with meats, fish, produce & food stalls.

sights.name: Pinchuk Art Centre
sights.quote: Contemporary art gallery within a historic building, with 6 floors including a video-lounge & cafe.
sights.address: вул. Велика Васильківська, Baseina St, 1, 3-2, Kyiv, Ukraine, 01004

sights.name: Kiev Funicular
sights.quote: Storied funicular along Volodymyrska Hill connecting the upper Old Town & lower Podil areas.

sights.name: One-Street Museum
sights.quote: Snug museum showcasing items from the 18th & 19th centuries, including manuscripts, photos & books.

sights.name: St. Michael's Vydubytsky Men's Monastery
sights.quote: Founded by the son of Yaroslav the Wise, Prince Vsevolod, this monastery is a symbol of Orthodoxy.

sights.name: Park of Eternal Glory
sights.quote: City park perched on top of a hill, with a memorial & the Tomb of the Unknown Soldier.
sights.address: Lavrska St, 15, Kyiv, Київська обл., Ukraine, 01015

sights.name: Holosiivskyi National Natural Park
sights.quote: Sprawling national park featuring forest steppe landscapes, trails, ponds, playgrounds & eateries.

sights.name: Friendship of Nations Arch
sights.quote: Huge rainbow-shaped arch with a riverfront deck built in 1982 to honor Russia & the Ukraine.

sights.name: A.V. Fomin Botanical Garden
sights.quote: One of Ukraine's oldest botanic institutions with around 9,000 native & non-native plant species.

sights.name: Kiev Zoo
sights.quote: 40-hectare zoo with tigers, lions & collections of amphibians, reptiles, birds & invertebrates.

sights.name: Expo Center of Ukraine
sights.quote: Sprawling cultural space offering a variety of exhibits & vendors in a serene, parklike setting.
sights.address: Natsionalnyy Ekspotsentr Ukrainy, М01, Kyiv, Ukraine, 02000

sights.name: National Museum of Folk Architecture and Life of Ukraine
sights.orig_name: National Museum of Folk Architecture and Life of Ukraine
sights.quote: Traditional Ukrainian buildings cluster together at this open-air museum of traditional life.

sights.name: Hydropark
sights.quote: Bustling urban beach with cafes, discos, boat rides, volleyball & other recreation options.

sights.name: Museum of Water
sights.quote: Complex including old water towers & reservoirs, with displays on water including a children's area.

sights.name: Kyiv in miniature
sights.quote: Park with miniature scale models of Kiev's major streets, squares, churches, bridges & more.
sights.address: ст. Метро ГИДРОПАРК,Броварський проспект, 9-В біля Ресторану "Млин, біля, Kyiv, Ukraine, 02000

sights.name: National Museum of the History of Ukraine
sights.orig_name: National Museum of the History of Ukraine
sights.quote: Scientific museum with a collection of items ranging from prehistoric artifacts to folk art.

sights.name: National Art Museum of Ukraine
sights.quote: 19th-century neo-classical museum with works ranging from medieval icons to 20th-century art.

sights.name: Chocolate house
sights.quote: Early 20th-century mansion with sculptures & ornate interiors in styles from Moorish to Byzantine.

sights.name: Park Kyoto
sights.quote: Japan-themed park with spring cherry blossoms lining footpaths, plus a rock garden & stone pagodas.
